The string of the raw state is already in the variable `state` so do not repeat the state in the code. Code: ```python from bs4 import BeautifulSoup # parse the HTML state soup = BeautifulSoup(state, 'html.parser') # Find all tab content divs tabs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'ui-tabs-panel'}) for idx, tab in enumerate(tabs, 1): if tab.find('span', string="integer."): obs = f'Click on the link "integer." in Tab #{idx}' break ``` Write code within three backticks '```' to Switch between the tabs to find and click on the link "morbi". output:

```python
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
# parse the HTML state
soup = BeautifulSoup(state, 'html.parser')
# Find all tab content divs
tabs = soup.find_all('div', {'class': 'ui-tabs-panel'})
for idx, tab in enumerate(tabs, 1):
    if tab.find('span', string="Arcu"):
        obs = f'Click on the link "Arcu" in Tab #{idx}'
        break
```
